			<div class="blogComment">
				&nbsp;<br /><a name="115378061010578311"></a> 
				Orcmid, what a wonderful post, and adventure. Susan and I left Rye early Friday morning to catch a plane to Minneapolis and a friend's wedding. The day started wonderfully, and we were speeding down I-95 on the way to Laguardia airport when just before Exit 16 all traffic stopped. We learned from the radio that a collision between two trucks had the entire road closed for seven miles. So we had our own adventure, using some local knowledge of side streets, alternate road and bridges to get to the airport and our gate with 15 min to spare. A two hour rain delay on tarmac followed, but we arrived in good time and, like you and Vicki, had a very nice time indeed.<BR/><BR/>That there are no ordinary moments is a most ordinary fact of life.<br />
